+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Classified every visible review thread from `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` before editing code, then remediated only the actionable items on the current branch.
+
+## Thread Disposition
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete outdated-hunk suggestion
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+The canonical machine-readable triage is recorded in `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`.
+
+## Changes Made
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+  - Normalizes the incoming approval state before calling `build_preview_payload`.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`
+  - Preserves `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in the `preview_unavailable` fallback payload.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`
+  - Adds regression coverage for `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"` through `build_policy_preview(...)`.
+  - Extends the existing fallback test to assert the preserved approval metadata.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`
+  - Updates the fallback example to the corrected payload shape and documents why approval metadata remains present.
+
+## Verification
+
+Ran:
+
+```bash
+python -m pytest tests/test_preview.py tests/test_approval_router.py
+```
+
+Result: `5 passed`
+
+## Guardrails Kept
+
+- Did not modify `.github/review_export/`, `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md`, `tests/test_approval_router.py`, `AGENTS.md`, `Dockerfile`, `.scenario_variant`, `release_context/`, or `incident_context/`.
+- Did not add `legacy_preview_hint`.
