+## T-214-01
+
+Applied. `src/policy/preview.py` now preserves `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` even when `preview_enabled=False`, so the fallback payload keeps the same approval contract as the live preview path.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. This was the same reopened fallback-payload regression, so the fix landed once in `src/policy/preview.py` and no separate code change was needed.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Not applied. The suggestion targeted an outdated hunk in `src/policy/approval_router.py`, and reviving a legacy preview branch would reintroduce deprecated behavior on the current branch.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Applied. `tests/test_preview.py` now includes a regression that exercises `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)` and asserts the fallback payload returns `approval_state="human_review_required"` with `requires_human_review=True`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Applied. `docs/approval_policy.md` now shows the corrected fallback payload, including `approval_state="human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review: true`.
